Reasoning: The paper presents distributed algorithms for maximum independent set and maximum matching problems in the CONGEST model, which is a well-studied model in distributed computing. The paper also discusses the round complexity of the algorithms, which is a common metric in distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves graph theory and approximation algorithms, which are relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.AL (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the use of coloring, which is a common technique in network algorithms, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a likely sub-category as well.
